{{Infobox book <!-- |italic title = (see above) --> | name = Beyond Oil: The View from Hubbert's Peak | image = Beyond Oil by Deffeyes.jpg | image_size = | caption = Hardcover edition | alt = | author = [[Kenneth S. Deffeyes]] | title_orig = | translator = | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = United States | language = English | series = | subject = | genre = Non-fiction | publisher = [[Hill and Wang]] | publisher2 = | pub_date = February 24, 2005 | english_pub_date = | media_type = Print, e-book | pages = 224 pp. | awards = | isbn = 978-0809029563 | oclc = | dewey = | congress = | preceded_by = | followed_by = | wikisource = }}
'''''Beyond Oil: The View from Hubbert's Peak''''' is a 2006 book by [[Kenneth S. Deffeyes]]. Deffeyes is a [[geologist]] who warned of the coming [[2000s energy crisis|oil crisis]] in a previous book called ''[[Hubbert's Peak]]''.
==Overview== In this book, he explores the Earth's supply of potential replacement fuels. ''Beyond Oil'' evaluates a range of energy sources, from [[petroleum]] to [[hydrogen]], and evaluates the advantages and disadvantages of each.<ref>[http://www.thefiniteworld.com/node/43 Book Review: “Beyond Oil: The View from Hubbert’s Peak”]{{deadlink|date=March 2015}}</ref><ref>[http://www.ecobooks.com/books/beyondoil.htm Beyond Oil: The View from Hubbert's Peak]</ref>
