The '''Sustainable Dairying: Water Accord''' is a voluntary agreement signed by leading participants of [[Dairy farming in New Zealand|New Zealand's dairy industry]] in 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dairynz.co.nz/media/3286407/sustainable-dairying-water-accord-2015.pdf|title=Sustainable Dairying: Water Accord|publisher=DairyNZ}}</ref> It serves as a successor to the 2003 [[Dairying and Clean Streams Accord]].

